lead_paragraph: John Wall scored 16 of his 37 points in the fourth quarter, Marcin Gortat added 18 points and a career-high 20 rebounds, and the Washington Wizards rallied for a 116-108 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night.

headline.print_headline: Wall Scores 37 as Wizards Rally to Beat 76ers 116-108
